Field Label:
Instructions

1. All mice in the data entry form are given a number 0,1,3,10,30

2. If more than one cage is to be used for a group then use the group name followed by a letter, as such - Test 1A

3. If numbers such as 2P, 4,11,13,40 are to be used they will corespond to 0,1,3,10,30 on this data entry form and will always belong to the second group, as such - Test 1B

4. If multiple conditions are to be entered into a single field then they must be delimited by a comma-space

Notes

First Instance of BLI form gives an error, just click through, I haven't found a solution for this, it will not affect the data

Chemical Conditioning is curently in the beta stage, contact Jake if you need this for an experiment

This form cannot accomodate multiple sources of bone marrow and t-cells, the maximum number of donors is two

Other "custom" experimental add ons are currently in development

MURINE Database Inclusion

Direct any questions about dataset inclusion to

Jake Fischman, Nicholas Waters, or Tyler Funnell
